An Act relating to the Oklahoma Turnpike Authority;
7
requiring the Oklahoma Turnpike Authority to develop
8
and submit certain plan; requiring certain plan be
8
submitted by certain date; providing penalty for
9
certain violations; providing for codification;
9
providing an effective date; and declaring an
10
emergency.
10
11
11
12
12
13
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13
14
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14
15
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1701.1 of Title 69, unless there
15
16
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16
17
A. The Oklahoma Turnpike Authority shall develop and submit a
17
18
comprehensive plan for its orderly dissolution and disbandment. The
18
19
plan shall include, at a minimum, provisions for the:
19
20
1. Liquidation of assets;
20
21
2. Transfer of all turnpike infrastructure and road inventory
21
22
to the Department of Transportation;
22
23
23
24
24
Req. No. 3107 Page 1

1
3. Application of any surplus funds toward the retirement of
1
2
outstanding debts, prioritizing obligations with the highest
2
3
interest rates; and
3
4
4. A detailed cost-benefit analysis of such proposed
4
5
dissolution, including fiscal impacts to the state and ratepayers.
5
6
B. 1. The Authority shall electronically submit the completed
6
7
plan to the Legislature and the Governor no later than December 31,
7
8
2027.
8
9
2. Upon failure of the Authority to submit such plan by the
9
10
required date, or if such plan is deemed incomplete or inadequate by
10
11
joint resolution of the Legislature, the Authority shall be
11
12
prohibited from issuing any new bonds, increasing toll rates, or
12
13
initiating new construction projects until the plan is submitted or
13
14
is deemed complete by joint resolution of the Legislature.
14
15
3. In addition to such prohibitions provided for in paragraph 2
15
16
of this subsection, the Authority shall be subject to a civil
16
17
penalty of One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00) per day for each day
17
18
until such plan is submitted or is deemed complete by joint
18
19
resolution of the Legislature. The Attorney General is authorized
19
20
to enforce the provisions of this paragraph through civil action.
20
21
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
21
22
SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
22
23
of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
